windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 884 to 903?
A) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
B) Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.
C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

options.A: Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
options.B: Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.
options.C: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

windows.answer: B) Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.

windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 1321 to 1351?
A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
B) Shake anomaly: The time series exhibits sudden, uncharacteristic fluctuations.
C) Sudden Increase anomaly: Values show an unexpected surge relative to adjacent points.

options.A: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.B: Shake anomaly: The time series exhibits sudden, uncharacteristic fluctuations.
options.C: Sudden Increase anomaly: Values show an unexpected surge relative to adjacent points.

windows.answer: A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
